'''Baja Broadband''' was a [[cable television]] provider based in [[Alamogordo, New Mexico]] with subscribers in [[Arizona]], [[Colorado]], [[Nevada]], [[New Mexico]], [[Texas]] and [[Utah]]. The company was acquired on August 2, 2013, by [[Telephone and Data Systems]], a [[Fortune 1000]] company.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.telecompetitor.com/tds-acquires-baja-broadband-for-267-5-million |title=TDS Acquires Baja Broadband for $267.5 Million - 2013-08-02 15:12:00 &#124; Telecompeitor |publisher=telecompetitor.com |date=2013-08-02|accessdate=2013-08-02}}</ref> It was renamed TDS in 2015.<ref>{{Cite web| title = Baja Broadband officially becomes TDS today| work = TDS Recent News Releases - TDS Telecom| accessdate = 2016-12-02| url = https://tdstelecom.com/about/news/categories/tds/baja-broadband-officially-becomes-tds-today.html}}</ref>
Baja Broadband was known as Orange Broadband until 2007. Most of Baja Broadband's systems were former [[Charter Communications]] systems acquired in 2006<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.multichannel.com/article/88070-43_7K_Charter_Subs_Turning_Orange.php |title=43.7K Charter Subs Turning Orange - 2006-03-22 12:23:00 &#124; Multichannel News |publisher=Multichannel.com |date=2006-03-22 |accessdate=2012-08-27}}</ref> and [[US Cable]] systems acquired in 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.multichannel.com/article/472689-QUICK_HITS.php |title=QUICK HITS - 2011-08-22 04:01:00 &#124; Multichannel News |publisher=Multichannel.com |date= |accessdate=2012-08-27}}</ref>
