{{Infobox company | name = Digi TV | logo = Digitv logo.png | logo_size = 260px | type = [[Private company|Private]] | slogan = | foundation = 2004 | location = [[Bucharest]], [[Romania]] | key_people = | | industry = [[Telecommunication]] | products = [[Direct broadcast satellite]] | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | num_employees = | parent = [[RCS & RDS]] | subsid = | homepage = [http://www.digitv.ro/ www.digitv.ro] | footnotes = }}
'''Digi TV''' is a [[Romania]]n [[Direct To Home|DTH]] platform. It belongs to the [[RCS & RDS]], one of the biggest [[telecommunication]] operators in [[South-Eastern Europe]] and the largest [[satellite television|satellite]] and [[cable television]] company in [[Romania]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dark-fiber.tmcnet.com/topics/dark-fiber/articles/309297-eci-telecom-rcs-rds-deploy-100g-channels-romania.htm |title= ECI Telecom and RCS & RDS Deploy 100G Channels in Romania |publisher=Dark Fiber Community |date=September 26, 2012}}</ref>
== Availability == * [[Romania]] – since December 2004 * [[Hungary]] – since February 2006 * [[Czech Republic]] – since August 2006 * [[Serbia]] – since November 2006
== Broadcasting and encryption == Digi TV broadcasts from [[Thor 6]] and Intelsat 10-02 satellites, at a position of 0,8° W. Channels are encrypted in [[Nagravision]] encryption system.
