'''Ivan Radunsky''' (1872 &ndash; 1955) played the part of Bim in the clown duo of [[Bim Bom]].<ref name="Room2010">{{cite book|author=Adrian Room|title=Dictionary of Pseudonyms: 13,000 Assumed Names and Their Origins, 5th ed.|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=eSIhzKnNUf4C&pg=PA61|date=1 July 2010|publisher=McFarland|isbn=978-0-7864-5763-2|pages=61–62}}</ref> He was the founder of that duo.<ref name="Ėrdman1995">{{cite book|author=Nikolaĭ Robertovich Ėrdman|title=A Meeting about Laughter: Sketches, Interludes, and Theatrical Parodies|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=L94GUDmAQq0C&pg=PA28|year=1995|publisher=Psychology Press|isbn=978-3-7186-5580-9|page=28}}</ref>

He was a Pole by birth.<ref name="Room2010"/>

