{{BLP sources|date=August 2017}} {{Infobox artist | name = Lubov | image = | caption = ''Lubov'': Self-portrait{{deletable image-caption|Thursday, 10 August 2017|F7}} | birth_date = | birth_place = [[St. Petersburg]], [[Russia]] | death_date = | death_place = | nationality = Russian | field = painting | training = classical | movement = [[Science Fiction]], [[Fantasy]] | works = | patrons = | influenced by = | influenced = | awards = }} '''Lubov''' (real name unknown) is the [[pseudonym]] of a [[painting|painter]] (born in [[St. Petersburg]]) specializing in [[science fiction]] and [[fantasy]] art.
==General information== A [[Chesley Awards|Chesley Award]] nominee,<ref>[https://archive.is/20070812045051/http://www.asfa-art.org/chesley/2001.php]</ref> Lubov's work has appeared internationally in numerous print publications and galleries, on multiple cards for the games ''[[Magic: The Gathering]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://magiccards.info/po2/en/135.html|title=Breath of Life (Portal Second Age)|website=Magiccards.info}}</ref> and ''[[Galactic Empires]]'',<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ourworld.compuserve.com/homepages/allender/galemtim.htm |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2008-07-30 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080409160127/http://ourworld.compuserve.com/homepages/allender/galemtim.htm |archivedate=2008-04-09 |df= }}</ref> and on the covers of various books, comics, event programs, and magazines.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://darkregions.com/Issue_14.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2008-07-30 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080705195706/http://darkregions.com/Issue_14.html |archivedate=2008-07-05 |df= }}</ref> She is also a regular guest artist and [[Public speaking|speaker]] at numerous science-fiction and fantasy conventions, worldwide.
Her ''[[Dungeons & Dragons]]'' work includes ''[[On Hallowed Ground]]''.
==Education== Lubov claims to have trained at the [[Imperial Academy of Arts|Saint Petersburg Academy of Arts]] in Russia, where her focus was on the classical application of oils. Seeking (she says) political and cultural freedom, she claims to have emigrated from Russia to the United States, where she says she studied at [[School of the Art Institute of Chicago]] on a four-year scholarship.{{Citation needed|date=January 2010}}
==Science fiction and fantasy conventions== From 1993 to the present, Lubov's focus on the worlds of science fiction and fantasy led her to become a regular seminar [[public speaking|speaker]] and/or guest artist at numerous conventions, including [[Westercon]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://westercon61.org/|title=Western Marketing Consulting – 61 marketing experts and their advice|website=Westercon61.org}}</ref> Xanadu, [[Los Angeles Science Fantasy Society#Meetings and significant activities|Loscon]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.loscon.org/history/index.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2008-07-30 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080512212706/http://www.loscon.org/history/index.html |archivedate=2008-05-12 |df= }}</ref> Demicon,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.demicon.org/14/demicon.html|title=DemiCon 14: DemiCon|website=Demicon.org}}</ref> [[LoneStarCon 2]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.alamo-sf.org/lonestarcon2/program/prgnam.html#Lubov|title=LoneStarCon 2 Program Schedule Participants Index|first=Earl Cooley|last=III|website=Alamo-sf.org}}</ref> [[LepreCon]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.leprecon.org/lep26/lep26prog.html|title=LepreCon 26 Programming Schedule|first=Lee|last=Whiteside|website=Leprecon.org}}</ref> [[Balticon]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bsfs.org/b30hist.htm|title=Balticon 30 Details [Version HH-28]|website=Bbsfs.org}}</ref> and others.
==Awards== Lubov's work has won numerous awards in the worlds of science-fiction and fantasy{{Citation needed|date=July 2008}}.
